>>Would removing ric-ipareplica (CentOS 7, Dogtag down) from the topology first be a prerequisite before the fresh install?
I'd recommend against removing anything prior to installing new replicas, even if pki-tomcat is currently down. The replica may still be servicing ldap requests.

*IF* you want to keep the current environment (e.g., the current ldap database as-is), the next steps are to introduce new replicas, and then start decommissioning
the old centOS machines, and the last step would be to replace the rhel-8.10 with another rhel-9.

You'd just have to be aware of transferring the roles appropriately in the process as documented in this doc:
https://docs.redhat.com/en/documentation/red_hat_enterprise_linux/9/html/migrating_to_identity_management_on_rhel_9/index

